<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,618,151,177]" box="[151,618,151,177]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,618,151,177]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,618,151,177]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Marikovskij, 1961" authorityName="Marikovskij" authorityYear="1961" box="[238,618,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Careopalpis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,383,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Careopalpis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marikovskij" box="[390,618,151,177]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Marikovskij, P. I. (1961) New gall midges (Diptera, Itonididae) from south-eastern Kazakhstan. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie 40, 37 - 50. [in Russian]. English translation in Entomological Review 40, 16 - 22." type="journal article" year="1961">
Marikovskij, 
<number box="[559,618,151,177]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1961.0">1961</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,226,452]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName box="[151,295,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Careopalpis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,295,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Careopalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an Old World genus of the tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[723,868,226,252]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Lasiopterini">Lasiopterini</taxonomicName>
, currently comprising 
<number box="[1137,1166,226,252]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="14.0">14</number>
species, all associated with 
<taxonomicName box="[211,405,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Chenopodiaceae</taxonomicName>
in Eastern Europe and Central Asia. Adults are small, stout, and very uniform morphologically. The female ovipositor is characterized by a ventrally curved aculeus, a fusiform apical lamella, and a lateral plate bearing relatively long and curved setae. The ovipositor is shorter than in the related genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Baldratia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Baldratia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the number of antennal flagellomeres rarely deviates from 
<quantity box="[958,1021,386,412]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="in" value="10.0">10 in</quantity>
both sexes, and flagellomeres are never fused. Palpus is one-segmented. Larvae do not have a spatula.
</paragraph>
